FBIS4-46120 "jptot022__l94029" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 21 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction `Believer's Resistance' Head TA2105043694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0405 GMT 21 May 94 TA2105043694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Last night, an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] force operating deep in Lebanon's al-Biqa' region captured and brought to Israel Mustafa al-Dirani, the head of a radical terrorist organization which took navigator Ron Arad captive in 1986. Al- Dirani heads an organization called the Believer's Resistance. An IDF spokesman reported that all our forces returned safely to base. A REUTERS reporter in al-Biqa' reported that an IDF force flew by helicopter to al-Dirani's village of Qasr al-Nabah), which is located 10 kilometers from Zahlah. The commando force kidnapped al- Dirani from his home. IDF representatives have informed the Arad family about the operation.
